      "关键词": ["Long-Context Language Models", "Retrieval-Augmented Generation", "Summarization", "Evaluation", "Synthetic Data Generation", "Query-Focused Summarization", "Citation Evaluation"],
      "摘要": "This paper introduces SummHay, a benchmark task for evaluating long-context language models (LLMs) and retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems. SummHay involves summarizing insights from a large corpus of synthesized documents (the 'Haystack') in response to specific queries, with the requirement to cite source documents. The authors generate Haystacks in two domains (conversations and news), each containing about 100k tokens. They evaluate 10 LLMs and 50 RAG systems on SummHay, finding that even with oracle retrieval signals, current systems lag behind estimated human performance by over 10 points on a joint score of coverage and citation quality. The benchmark also reveals trade-offs between RAG and long-context LLMs, position bias in models, and the effectiveness of advanced RAG components.",
